<HR><H2>[COLD] Implementing telnet</H2>
<H3>daemon@ATHENA.MIT.EDU (Mon Dec  2 18:30:56 1996
)</H3>
<PRE>
Date: Mon, 02 Dec 1996 15:26:55 -0800
To: coldstuff@cold.org
From: Jeff Kesselman &lt;jeffk@ten.net&gt;

P.S.

Do NOT implement EITHER a telnet server OR client UNLESS you are committed
to a FULL telnet protocol implementation.  There are far too many things
out there already that CALL themselves telnet that do NOT talk real telnet
protocol.
(Like, 95% of all Win95 "telnet" programs.)

(Kin you tell I been through this frustration?  This is what killed my
first cold windowing project.)

Jeff Kesselman
</PRE>
